Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

01:55.282 --> 01:58.950
[laughing]

01:58.952 --> 02:02.320
- Uh-oh.
- Uh-oh.

02:07.493 --> 02:09.494
- [gasps]

02:09.496 --> 02:11.930
- Hey, spongebob.
- Yes, patrick?

02:11.932 --> 02:15.533
- Do you know how to swim?
- No.

02:15.535 --> 02:16.167
- Me neither.

02:16.169 --> 02:18.336
- Hmm, I wonder why
we're not sinking to the bottom

02:18.338 --> 02:19.103
Of goo lagoon.

02:19.105 --> 02:22.340
- [screaming]
- patrick, you're floating!

02:22.342 --> 02:24.676
- Oh.

02:24.678 --> 02:27.412
Hey! You're floating too!

02:27.414 --> 02:28.112
What happened?

02:28.114 --> 02:30.248
- These weird bubbles
saved us.

02:30.250 --> 02:32.951
- It's all purple.
And sticky.

02:32.953 --> 02:35.219
- And it's really stretchy.

02:35.221 --> 02:37.155
It's some kind of goo bubble.

02:37.157 --> 02:41.025
- [sniffs]
the smell makes my nose tickle.

02:41.027 --> 02:43.695
Ah, ah, ah, ah...

02:43.697 --> 02:45.697
Choo!

02:45.699 --> 02:49.267
[laughing]
hey, it bounces!

02:49.269 --> 02:52.870
[both cackling]

02:58.344 --> 02:59.310
- [gasps]

02:59.312 --> 03:01.746
Ooh.
[sighs]

03:01.748 --> 03:03.948
[gasps]
- sorry!

03:05.150 --> 03:07.952
- Ah! Ha ha ha!

03:13.792 --> 03:16.327
[patrick chuckling]

03:21.867 --> 03:25.903
- Chum!
Get your red-hot chum here!

03:25.905 --> 03:27.405
What's the deal?

03:27.407 --> 03:28.740
According to my algorithm,

03:28.742 --> 03:32.643
Beach-goers should be famished
and looking for a treat.

03:32.645 --> 03:35.446
A treat like chum!
Hello!

03:35.448 --> 03:38.783
It's perfectly edible, people.

03:39.752 --> 03:41.486
Oh, come on, man!

03:41.488 --> 03:43.521
This is my livelihood!

03:43.523 --> 03:44.589
- [sighs]

03:44.591 --> 03:45.990
A beautiful day
beachside.

03:45.992 --> 03:49.327
I couldn't think of a thing
that could ruin this.

03:49.329 --> 03:51.629
- I could think of a few.

03:56.335 --> 03:59.303
Hey.
You're blocking my light.

03:59.305 --> 04:00.571
- [yelling]

04:00.573 --> 04:03.307
- [gasps]

04:03.309 --> 04:05.743
Spongebob.

04:05.745 --> 04:07.111
[screaming]

04:07.113 --> 04:08.880
[patrick chuckles]

04:09.481 --> 04:11.315
- Ah, sweet karma.

04:11.317 --> 04:14.519
It can come from
the most boneheaded of places.

04:14.521 --> 04:18.423
[patrick and spongebob
giggling]

04:18.425 --> 04:19.791
Wait a second.

04:19.793 --> 04:22.026
What are those bouncing blobs
of goo?

04:22.028 --> 04:25.530
- [grunts]
I don't know, and I don't care.

04:25.532 --> 04:29.300
[both cackling]

04:29.302 --> 04:31.002
Hold it!

04:31.004 --> 04:33.938
What I wanna know
is why you two have ruined

04:33.940 --> 04:36.641
My attempts
at having an even tan.

04:36.643 --> 04:37.575
- Oh, sorry, squidward.

04:37.577 --> 04:39.844
We're riding
on these cool goo bubbles.

04:39.846 --> 04:42.046
They're floating
out of goo lagoon.

04:42.048 --> 04:43.714
[metal clanking]

04:43.716 --> 04:47.785
[electronic pulses]

04:47.787 --> 04:50.888
All: Aaaaaah!

04:55.227 --> 04:59.030
- Stop!
Those bubbles are dangerous!

04:59.032 --> 05:00.264
- Dangerous?

05:00.266 --> 05:02.233
- Fascinating.
Tell us more.

05:02.235 --> 05:05.103
- Yeah, but with visual aids.

05:05.105 --> 05:08.539
- Okay.

05:08.541 --> 05:10.675
My scientific investigation
has revealed

05:10.677 --> 05:12.743
That deep beneath
the lagoon floor

05:12.745 --> 05:15.880
Is a volcanic pocket
of super goo.

05:15.882 --> 05:16.614
A crack has formed,

05:16.616 --> 05:18.916
Releasing bubbles of the goop
to the surface,

05:18.918 --> 05:21.786
Which are toxic
and very unstable.

05:21.788 --> 05:25.056
At any moment,
it could lose its integrity,

05:25.058 --> 05:28.392
And boom!
It'll explode.

05:28.394 --> 05:29.961
- That rodent's right.

05:29.963 --> 05:33.931
A giant goo bubble could really
level the playing field.

05:33.933 --> 05:36.968
If someone were able
to control its power,

05:36.970 --> 05:39.871
They'd control all
of bikini bottom.

05:39.873 --> 05:43.875
And I'm gonna be
that someone.

