All: Thanks, goo.

07:41.961 --> 07:45.896
- And now we go
to perch perkins at the scene.

07:45.898 --> 07:47.431
- That's right,
perch perkins here

07:47.433 --> 07:49.934
At goo lagoon,
bringing you the latest

07:49.936 --> 07:51.335
On the super goo event.

07:51.337 --> 07:55.039
What do you think
of super goo, young man?

07:55.041 --> 07:57.708
- I'm on tv!

07:57.710 --> 08:02.380
- And you, sir.
What's your opinion?

08:02.382 --> 08:03.781
Uh, sir?

08:03.783 --> 08:05.182
- It's awesome.

08:05.184 --> 08:06.484
- Uh, that's great.

08:06.486 --> 08:09.120
Let's get some comments
from some other beach-goers.

08:09.122 --> 08:13.257
- I have a comment.
Super goo is evil!

08:13.259 --> 08:14.625
Stay in your homes!

08:14.627 --> 08:18.829
- Yes, sirree,
the goo bubbles certainly are

08:18.831 --> 08:20.298
Getting folks excited.

08:20.300 --> 08:23.067
Both: We sure are excited.

08:23.069 --> 08:25.102
[laughter]

08:25.104 --> 08:29.040
- I can't find this thing
anywhere.

08:29.042 --> 08:31.075
Come on now, think,
plankton.

08:31.077 --> 08:33.844
If you were a giant bubble
of dangerous goo,

08:33.846 --> 08:34.645
Where would you be?

08:34.647 --> 08:37.081
- Sheldon, this ship
wasn't designed

08:37.082 --> 08:38.316
To reach these depths.

08:38.318 --> 08:39.784
- That's great,
sweetheart.

08:39.785 --> 08:41.818
- If you continue this search
much longer,

08:41.821 --> 08:44.288
Your power supply will deplete
and you'll sink.

08:44.290 --> 08:47.758
- All right, karen,
I'll make sure I write that down

08:47.760 --> 08:48.759
In my book titled

08:48.761 --> 08:50.995
<i>Insignificant things</i>
<i>my wife told me.</i>

08:50.997 --> 08:53.464
- Whatever.
Go get stuck at the bottom

08:53.466 --> 08:54.031
Of goo lagoon.

08:54.033 --> 08:56.033
It's your funeral.
- What did you say?

08:56.035 --> 09:00.037
- I said, go get stuck
at the bottom of goo lagoon.

09:00.039 --> 09:00.771
- That's it, karen!

09:00.773 --> 09:03.174
The goo bubble must be stuck
at the bottom.

09:03.176 --> 09:04.575
We just have to
get down there.

09:04.577 --> 09:08.779
Karen, cut the power
to the entire ship.

09:08.781 --> 09:09.780
Yes.

09:09.782 --> 09:13.250
[sinister laughter]

09:13.252 --> 09:14.785
Look, there it is.

09:14.787 --> 09:18.856
Karen, fire up
the engine power.

09:18.858 --> 09:20.825
With my mechanical
clam digger,

09:20.827 --> 09:24.895
I'll crack open this goo-cano
easy as a clam.

09:24.897 --> 09:26.497
Which is what
it was built for,

09:26.499 --> 09:30.334
So, you know,
that makes sense.

09:30.336 --> 09:34.238
[sinister laughter]

09:34.240 --> 09:36.173
Yes. <i>Yes!</i>

09:36.175 --> 09:39.410
Bubble forth,
my gooey wrath!

09:39.412 --> 09:40.611
[earth rumbling]

09:40.613 --> 09:44.248
And now to get the ding dang
out of here.

09:44.250 --> 09:48.486
[earth rumbling]

09:48.488 --> 09:50.788
- Look!

09:50.790 --> 09:52.990
Giant goo bubble!

09:52.992 --> 09:56.394
- See, I told ya!
[panting]

09:56.396 --> 09:59.029
Run for your life!

09:59.031 --> 10:02.233
- Sandy's really
getting out of hand.

10:04.136 --> 10:05.169
- This is perch perkins
reporting live

10:05.171 --> 10:06.771
From goo lagoon,
where I'm standing

10:06.773 --> 10:09.974
In front of what appears to be
some sort of gigantic,

10:09.976 --> 10:12.910
Gooey bubble
rising out of the water

10:12.912 --> 10:14.445
Into the water.

10:14.447 --> 10:15.546
With me is sandy cheeks.

10:15.548 --> 10:18.749
Miss cheeks, as bikini bottom's
resident know-it-all,

10:18.751 --> 10:20.484
We look to you
for answers.

10:20.486 --> 10:21.886
Who? What? How?
Why? When?

10:21.888 --> 10:24.455
- Well, perch,
I won't really know anything

10:24.457 --> 10:27.324
Until I run some tests,
but I can tell you

10:27.326 --> 10:28.626
It's pretty serious.

10:28.628 --> 10:31.462
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I need to get going.

10:31.464 --> 10:35.566
- Oh, yes. Of course.

10:35.568 --> 10:39.303
This is perch perkins,
and I'm soaking wet.

10:39.305 --> 10:40.404
Back to you.

10:40.406 --> 10:42.406
- Wow, it's so big.

10:42.408 --> 10:45.075
- That there's
a texas-size bubble!

10:45.077 --> 10:48.112
First, we'll check
its tensile strength.

10:48.114 --> 10:51.015
[thuds echo]
tight as a drum.

10:51.017 --> 10:53.350
- Oh, I wanna play
the drum!

10:53.352 --> 10:56.053
- No, patrick, don't!
That thing's volatile.

10:56.055 --> 10:59.790
There's no telling what kind of
damage it'll cause if it pops.

10:59.792 --> 11:01.759
- Oh, fine. Here!

11:01.761 --> 11:05.129
I don't need
that old stick anyways.

11:05.131 --> 11:06.564
[grunts]

11:09.267 --> 11:12.169
- Come on, guys, we still have
more tests to perform.

11:12.171 --> 11:13.938
I need a sample.
Be a darling

11:13.940 --> 11:16.974
And hand me that there bucket.

11:16.976 --> 11:18.375
[doink doink]

11:18.377 --> 11:20.444
[pop]

11:20.446 --> 11:22.813
[goo squishing]

11:22.815 --> 11:23.347
Okay, spongebob,

11:23.349 --> 11:28.152
Put a little of that gloop
in this analyzer.

11:28.154 --> 11:34.458
[beeps, blips]

11:34.460 --> 11:35.593
[power sputtering]

11:35.595 --> 11:37.161
This is worse
than I thought.

11:37.163 --> 11:39.396
- Look, sandy.
[laughter]

11:39.398 --> 11:41.065
- How many times
do I have to tell you

11:41.067 --> 11:41.799
That stuff's dangerous?

11:41.801 --> 11:44.101
Now, how are y'all gonna
clean that gunk off?

11:44.103 --> 11:45.769
- Oh, yeah. Gross.

11:45.771 --> 11:49.507
Good thing I keep
a spare set of hands.

11:52.077 --> 11:54.912
- Oh, yeah.

11:54.914 --> 11:58.682
- Uh, I have a better idea.

11:58.684 --> 12:01.952
Hold out your hands.

12:03.288 --> 12:05.422
- Ooh, they shine.

12:05.424 --> 12:07.324
- Well, it seems
to have stabilized.

12:07.326 --> 12:09.593
- As long as it doesn't get
any bigger,

12:09.595 --> 12:11.929
There's not too much
to worry about.

12:11.931 --> 12:13.330
[rumbling]

12:13.332 --> 12:15.199
That ain't good.

12:15.201 --> 12:19.169
All: Aaaaahh...

12:22.173 --> 12:24.575
- So, miss cheeks,
what's the prognosis?

12:24.577 --> 12:26.877
- Well, perch,
it's my considered opinion

12:26.879 --> 12:28.579
That now would be
a good time to...

12:28.581 --> 12:32.016
[rumbling]
run like heck!

12:32.018 --> 12:32.983
[all shouting]

12:32.985 --> 12:34.318
- Well, there you have it.

12:34.320 --> 12:37.121
This is perch perkins,
about to be swallowed

12:37.123 --> 12:38.522
By a giant wave.

12:38.524 --> 12:39.957
[emergency tone]

12:39.959 --> 12:45.029
[earth rumbling,
all shouting]

12:45.397 --> 12:49.433
- I'll catch up.
I gotta use the can.

12:51.636 --> 12:54.104
- Whoa.

12:56.641 --> 12:59.043
- Unh!

13:02.213 --> 13:05.382
Whew! That was a close one.

13:05.384 --> 13:07.918
- Help! Help!

13:07.920 --> 13:09.720
Heeelp!

13:09.722 --> 13:13.591
I'm out of toilet paper
in here.

13:14.859 --> 13:16.694
- Look out!

13:18.430 --> 13:20.030
- Aah!

13:20.032 --> 13:24.368
- Hang on, buddy.
Just a little bit more.

13:24.370 --> 13:26.804
Ah! Gotcha!

13:27.372 --> 13:30.374
Oh, I don't gotcha.
Aah!

13:34.279 --> 13:37.181
- Help!
[whimpering]

13:37.183 --> 13:38.215
- Now what do we do?

13:38.217 --> 13:41.819
- We need to get
to my submarine, fast.

13:42.387 --> 13:43.921
Squidward,
it's an emergency!

13:43.923 --> 13:46.090
I'm gonna need your bike.

13:46.092 --> 13:49.126
Hop on, spongebob.

13:51.830 --> 13:55.733
- Sheesh, you'd think
the sky was falling.

13:55.967 --> 14:00.137
I am going to learn
to keep my big mouth shut.

14:00.139 --> 14:03.207
- Aah! Aah!

14:03.209 --> 14:06.944
[laughing]

14:09.581 --> 14:12.883
Howdy, sponge...Blob.

14:12.885 --> 14:16.987
I'm so glad you could
<i>stick</i> around.

14:16.989 --> 14:18.989
[laughs]
<i>glad.</i>

14:18.991 --> 14:22.359
- Hold on, patrick.
We're here to rescue you.

14:22.361 --> 14:24.228
- Aw, go rescue
somebody else.

14:24.230 --> 14:29.466
Can't you see I'm playing
with my friend spongeblob?

14:32.103 --> 14:35.239
Don't worry,
I'll never leave you.

14:35.241 --> 14:36.674
Huh?

14:36.676 --> 14:38.242
Noooooo...

14:38.244 --> 14:40.911
Good-bye, spongeblob.

14:42.714 --> 14:45.749
Hi, spongebob.
Hi, sandy.

14:46.685 --> 14:47.584
- So what do we do now,
sandy?

14:47.586 --> 14:50.854
That thing is headed straight
for downtown bikini bottom.

14:50.856 --> 14:52.056
- If that thing pops,

14:52.058 --> 14:55.025
We can kiss
our beautiful town good-bye.

14:55.027 --> 14:58.696
- Good-bye.

14:58.698 --> 15:02.900
[all crying out]

15:04.969 --> 15:09.473
[wedding organ music,
people cheering]

15:09.475 --> 15:10.974
- Help me, my beloved.

15:10.976 --> 15:15.245
- Don't touch me,
you disgusting freak!

15:15.247 --> 15:20.150
Oh...My dress is ruined!

15:21.986 --> 15:23.454
- [gasps]

15:23.456 --> 15:28.425
- [laughing]
mommy goopy.

15:28.427 --> 15:29.993
- Aaaah!

15:29.995 --> 15:31.929
- [gasps]

15:33.798 --> 15:36.800
Whew.

15:38.203 --> 15:41.905
- Oh, no! It's headed
right for neptune's trident.

15:41.907 --> 15:44.608
- I was afraid
it might come to this.

15:44.610 --> 15:46.310
In order to save the city,

15:46.312 --> 15:49.313
We must destroy
public property.

15:49.315 --> 15:51.682
- Sandy, why do you have
missiles in your sub?

15:51.684 --> 15:54.785
- You know, in case
I get stuck in traffic.

15:54.787 --> 15:56.553
Here goes!

16:00.658 --> 16:02.659
Darn it!

16:03.661 --> 16:06.263
All: Aah!

16:06.265 --> 16:08.398
- Huh? What the--

16:08.400 --> 16:08.999
- That's weird.

16:09.001 --> 16:11.135
It's like that bubble
has a mind of its own.

16:11.137 --> 16:14.872
- Or the mind
of someone else. Look!

16:16.908 --> 16:18.942
- Whew.
- Plankton!

16:18.944 --> 16:21.011
I knew it.
- Yeah, it's me.

16:21.013 --> 16:22.279
What are y'all up to
this time?

16:22.281 --> 16:25.649
- Well, that's for me to know
and for you to <i>clam up!</i>

16:25.651 --> 16:27.084
- [gasps]
rude!

16:27.086 --> 16:29.987
- Let's just say
I've got big plans

16:29.989 --> 16:31.555
For this little bubble.

16:31.557 --> 16:35.759
[sinister laughter]

16:35.761 --> 16:42.232
- Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have to <i>goo.</i>

16:52.877 --> 16:53.610
[sinister laughter]

16:53.612 --> 16:56.313
- Dang it, we'll never
catch him at this rate.

16:56.315 --> 16:59.716
- Ha! They'll never catch me
at this rate.

16:59.718 --> 17:01.151
Oh!

17:01.153 --> 17:04.121
- Oh, no, you don't!

17:04.123 --> 17:06.156
Come here,
ya little varmint!

17:06.157 --> 17:09.159
You...Stay...Right...There!

17:09.161 --> 17:13.130
Yippee!
We got him now.

17:13.132 --> 17:15.965
- That's right.
Come to papa.

17:15.968 --> 17:17.467
- When we get you
out of there,

17:17.469 --> 17:19.803
You've got some explaining
to do.

17:19.805 --> 17:21.371
- Hey again, spongeblob.

17:21.373 --> 17:22.906
- We've got you surrounded,
plankton.

17:22.907 --> 17:25.275
Now come out
with your antennae in the air.

17:25.277 --> 17:28.145
- Oh, dear,
I guess you've got me.

17:28.146 --> 17:31.415
Oh, wait a second.
No, ya don't!

17:32.884 --> 17:35.085
- Retreat! Retreat!

17:35.087 --> 17:37.087
- Aw, don't go so soon.

17:37.089 --> 17:40.791
I hope you brought
your dancing shoes...

17:41.526 --> 17:46.363
'cause it's time to do
the electric goo boogaloo.

17:46.365 --> 17:49.967
[electricity crackling,
all shouting]

17:49.969 --> 17:52.402
[sinister laughter]

17:55.773 --> 17:58.375
All: Aaaahh...

17:58.377 --> 18:01.511
Whaaaa...
[thudding]

18:02.847 --> 18:05.749
- Good thing we landed
on spongebob.

18:05.751 --> 18:06.550
- Yeah, good thing.

18:06.552 --> 18:10.287
- Plankton, you creepy bacteria,
gimme back my sub!

18:10.289 --> 18:12.756
[whistling]

18:12.758 --> 18:15.692
[gasps]
my sub!

18:15.694 --> 18:16.393
- There, there, sandy.

18:16.395 --> 18:20.163
- Plankton, you're--
you're a big meanie weenie!

18:20.165 --> 18:22.065
You wouldn't be
such a tough guy

18:22.067 --> 18:23.767
Without that big ol' bubble!

18:23.769 --> 18:25.969
- Tough guy? Bubble?

18:25.971 --> 18:29.840
Patrick, eureka!
Inspiration.

18:29.842 --> 18:31.408
- Really?
[sniffs]

18:31.410 --> 18:33.210
Do I need deodorant?

18:33.212 --> 18:34.344
- No, but you're close.

18:34.346 --> 18:36.380
What we need is
liquid soap.

18:36.382 --> 18:39.650
It's time to fight bubble
with bubble.

18:39.652 --> 18:40.784
- Pbbbt! Bubbles!

18:40.786 --> 18:43.520
That's your answer
for everything.

18:43.522 --> 18:45.989
- Thank you.
Come again.

18:45.991 --> 18:50.527
Hey, who turned out
the lights?

18:50.529 --> 18:52.796
- Hello down there, krabs.

18:52.798 --> 18:55.966
Look, I brought you
a pretty balloon.

18:55.968 --> 18:58.235
And in return,
you can give me

18:58.237 --> 19:00.237
The krabby patty
secret formula.

19:00.239 --> 19:03.006
- Why in the world
would I want to do that?

19:03.008 --> 19:04.274
- 'cause if you don't,

19:04.276 --> 19:06.576
I'm gonna pop
this disgusting thing

19:06.578 --> 19:08.211
And destroy bikini bottom!

19:08.213 --> 19:11.415
As you can see,
I've projected the blast radius

19:11.417 --> 19:12.516
Of this goobombic balloon,

19:12.518 --> 19:15.585
And it's gonna cover
pretty much everything in town.

19:15.587 --> 19:18.989
- Oh, yeah?
Well, I can't see nothin'

19:18.991 --> 19:19.723
From down here.

19:19.725 --> 19:22.559
Oh, yeah, well look again,
ya dingus!

19:22.561 --> 19:24.061
- I won't be blackmailed!

19:24.063 --> 19:27.097
There's no way I'm giving you
me secret formuler.

19:27.099 --> 19:28.899
- You heard him,
bikini bottom.

19:28.901 --> 19:31.668
It's time to kiss clean
good-bye.

19:31.670 --> 19:34.604
[sinister laughter]
- hey, you!

19:34.606 --> 19:35.539
Yeah, you.

19:35.541 --> 19:37.507
Hold it right there, mister.

19:37.509 --> 19:38.241
- Eh, not again.

19:38.243 --> 19:41.178
- Prepare to meet your match,
you big bubble bully.

19:41.180 --> 19:43.780
- Well, this is interesting.
Let's see where it goes.

19:43.782 --> 19:47.217
- Thank neptune for the bargain
mart bulk discount.

19:47.219 --> 19:48.251
- Here goes.

19:48.253 --> 19:52.089
Geroni-blow!

19:52.091 --> 19:56.360
Pretty slick, huh?
Get him!

19:56.362 --> 19:58.695
- Huh? Uh-oh.

19:58.697 --> 20:00.364
- Whoo! Heh heh.
Oh, boy!

20:00.366 --> 20:02.366
Get him,
you big bubble bruiser.

20:02.368 --> 20:07.237
Whoo, ha! You're the man!
Yay.

20:13.945 --> 20:15.746
- Okay, where were we?

20:15.748 --> 20:18.482
Oh, yeah.

20:21.119 --> 20:22.786
- There goes a real hero.

20:22.788 --> 20:26.123
He gave his life
so we could stay clean.

20:29.761 --> 20:33.864
- [whimpering]

20:33.866 --> 20:37.134
<i>[the blue danube</i> plays]

20:37.136 --> 20:43.240
♪

20:43.242 --> 20:45.175
- Oh, no, he's coming back!

20:45.177 --> 20:47.944
- And he's heading
right for us!

20:49.847 --> 20:52.582
All: Aaaahh...

20:52.584 --> 20:53.850
[screech]

20:53.852 --> 20:55.886
- That's it!
No more messin' around.

20:55.888 --> 21:00.257
Gimme that formula, or I'll
destroy this stinkin' town!

21:00.259 --> 21:03.193
- [whining]
but I don't wanna.

21:03.195 --> 21:04.394
- You better do
what he says,

21:04.396 --> 21:06.329
Or we'll tear
your restaurant apart

21:06.331 --> 21:08.398
And give it to him ourselves.

21:08.400 --> 21:08.999
- Yeah.

21:09.001 --> 21:11.935
- I just washed my car!
- Yeah!

21:11.937 --> 21:15.906
- Rrrr...
Okay, I'll do it.

21:15.908 --> 21:18.809
- Yeah!

21:21.179 --> 21:23.947
- Here.
I hope you choke on it.

21:26.451 --> 21:28.652
- I can't believe it.

21:28.654 --> 21:32.122
After all these years,
it's mine!

21:32.124 --> 21:35.625
I'm so happy,
I could just burst.

21:35.627 --> 21:37.794
This bubble, that is.

21:37.796 --> 21:38.962
[all gasp]

21:38.964 --> 21:42.199
[sinister laughter]

21:44.702 --> 21:47.037
- Oh, that dirty little
double-timer!

21:47.039 --> 21:52.175
- Don't worry, he's about to get
what's coming to him.

21:53.744 --> 21:57.380
- Now to see what's inside
a krabby patty.

21:57.382 --> 22:01.184
"just one ingredient:"

22:01.186 --> 22:03.520
Darn it, krabs!

22:10.094 --> 22:11.328
Ow.

22:11.330 --> 22:12.295
- [laughs]

22:12.297 --> 22:15.866
- I don't see what you're
so gol-dern happy about.

22:15.868 --> 22:17.100
This is a catastrophe.

22:17.102 --> 22:19.369
- Well, darlin',
it's like this.

22:19.371 --> 22:20.670
Where you see disaster...

22:20.672 --> 22:23.106
[cash register rings]
I see dollar signs.

22:23.108 --> 22:29.279
So, spongebob, you got any
of the bubble soap left?

22:29.281 --> 22:32.115
Please have your money ready.

22:32.117 --> 22:33.683
Thank you.

22:33.685 --> 22:37.454
[cash register rings]
right this way.

22:46.797 --> 22:50.433
- See, patrick, bubbles <i>are</i>
the answer to everything.

22:50.435 --> 22:52.102
Ha ha ha ha ha.

